t not constantly anymore <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :faint --><img src=http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/smilies/faint.gif ALT=":faint"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Anyways..If you dont have this skill tied to your movement keys DO IT fast..You will never again have to tap that button, I also do this with foraging skills.<br>
<br>
1.Go to your 'action' window and click on the tab with the little thing that looks like a speech bubble.<br>
<br>
2. Click on the little arrow at the top of the tab till you find some empty buttons..right click on one<br>
<br>
3. type the following in the little screen <br>
            Name: skills (or something you'll remember)<br>
            first line:     /doability (number between 1 &amp; 6)  <br>
            second line: can be the same (another #)<br>
            Click : Accept<br>
<br>
Note: You can find out what number your sense heading ability is by checking your ability buttons tab<br>
<br>
- Just remember that if you tie a hot button slot to a certain key then ANYTIME you push that key whatever you have in that slot happens (this is why i have my button on ALL the tabs) It took me awhile to figure out why I kept casting spells when I moved before I figured that out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :grumpy --><img src=http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/smilies/pissed.gif ALT=":grumpy"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5. To tie it to movement - open your options screen ( it looks like a 'nut' as in nuts&amp; bolts) and find the options for your hot buttons. They should be numbered from 0 to 9. Next to the number there will be another slot that you can use to pick an alternate key to activate this button.<br>
<br>
In the slot next to the location where you have placed your new button click on the movement key on your keyboard (this can be any other movement key that you use)<br>
then close this window.<br>
<br>
If you were able to understand my directions and managed to follow them correctly what SHOULD happen is that everytime you hit the move botton you should AUTOMATICALLY be sensing heading (and /or foraging )  <br>
<br>
Sorry bout the double posting....was having some serious problems getting it to work  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :grumpy --><img src=http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/smilies/pissed.gif ALT=":grumpy"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Hope this helps! <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Koldriana ConstantlyLost</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
