<br>
If you are starting a new toon, here is how to max your sense heading very easily.  (I'm putting this here to benefit anyone starting a new toon or new to EQ)<br>
<br>
This technique is based on two observations: for the first few levels, it is easy to level quickly.  If your sense heading is within 5 of max for your level, (1+level)*5, it raises quickly.  <br>
Note that you will reach 200 skill at level 39, and your compass will become 100% reliable.  It gets dramatically more stable at 175 skill, BTW.<br>
<br>
1) You now automatically get max skill in your &quot;best&quot; weapon, so put 1 point in sense heading when you train your level 1 toon at his guild master.  <br>
<br>
2) In your skills tab, right click an empty box and select sense heading.  Drag and drop this to your hotbuttons. I suggest button #1.<br>
<br>
3) While you are turning in your newbie note and whatever in-town quests your race may have, constantly mash your sense heading hot key.  You should get a couple skill ups pretty quickly.  Then sit down and mash it until your skill is 10.<br>
<br>
4) Go kill a couple mobs and ding 2.<br>
<br>
5) From now on, while killing mobs, mash the sense heading key constantly during battle.  If you have bash or kick or you are a bard, you are going to be mashing hotkeys anyway.  I also mash it during travel, but that is actually optional - it just gets you through step 5 a bit quicker.  Once you have it maxed, you can stop mashing sense heading for that level.  This should actually happen in a suprisingly short amount of time if you are within 5 pts of max skill.   I haven't timed it but it seems to happen in the first 25% of my exp bar in early levels, and it can happen in the first blue bubble in later levels.<br>
<br>
6) If you are somehow close to leveling and haven't reached max skill in sense heading, sit down for 5 minutes and mash the key (or mash it while you run back to town to buy spells so you have them the instant you ding). <br>
<br>
It is very important to be at max before you ding.  That's the secret to very easily maxing sense heading.  If you rush through levels 1-10 without keeping it maxed, it will fall behind and you will be at level 11 with sense heading at 5 or 10 or even 25, and it will be a major pain to catch it up.  In Paludal Caverns, I was not able to max sense heading (or any other skill for that matter).  It fell behind by about 15 points.  I think it took 5 levels of constantly mashing sense heading during battle to catch back up - it is just that bad when you let it get more than 5 points from max!<br>
<br>
Or you can program sense heading into your movement keys and forever see lots of annoying messages. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;font-family:Tempus Sans ITC font;font-size:x-large;">Nikkon</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
